\fs21\fsmilli10995 Lesson 16: Immune System \'96 The Body\'92s Defenses\
The immune system is the body\'92s defense against germs and infections. It includes barriers like\
skin, and internal soldiers like white blood cells and antibodies that fight invaders. For example,\
if bacteria or viruses enter the body, immune cells recognize them and destroy them. The\
immune system also \'93remembers\'94 germs: after fighting an infection once, it can respond faster\
the next time. The immune system protects the body from antigens (germs like viruses and\
bacteria) and can react quicker if it has seen the germ before.\
