treatments.\
Afterward, learners will be able to distinguish bacteria from viruses. They will recall that bacteria\
are live cells and viruses are genetic particles that hijack cells. They should understand the\
basic idea that most colds and the flu are caused by viruses, while some illnesses like strep\
throat are caused by bacteria. This knowledge helps them see why different germs need\
different treatments.
