Medication: Rescue inhalers (like albuterol) act fast to open airways. Controllers (like inhaled\
steroids) reduce long-term inflammation but are taken daily.\
Lifestyle: Not smoking and avoiding secondhand smoke is critical, as smoke is a strong trigger.\
Staying active and healthy helps (with doctor\'92s guidance).\
