Safety: Doctors use the lowest radiation dose possible for X-rays. Protective shields (like\
aprons) protect other parts.\
Interpretation: A trained radiologist or doctor must read the images. You should always let\
doctors know if you might be pregnant before X-rays or CT scans.\
